            <td style="padding:0px 15px 0 0px;"><a href="#"></a>
            <h3 style="padding-top: 3px;"><a href="http://mj.unc.edu/StemblerLecture2015" target="_blank"><img src="/s/1723/images/gid8/editor/stembler_tnail.png" alt="" style="border-top: 8px solid #559fd3" width="300" height="200"></a><br>
            </h3>
            <h4>Nov. 6 homecoming event, the school's inaugural Stembler Lecture, to feature "Ant-Man" director and MPAA CEO &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</h4>
            <p>
            </p>
            <p style="font-family: wf_segoe-ui_normal, 'Segoe UI', 'Segoe WP', Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif; font-size:12px;">Movie industry executive John H. Stembler created a $3.25 million "game-changer" endowment for the school's broadcast program, funding a professorship, professionals in residence, capstone student experiences, lecture series and more. The inaugural Stembler Lecture will feature UNC alumnus and "Ant-Man" director Peyton Reed and Motion Picture Association of America chairman and CEO, former U.S. Sen. Chris Dodd.</p>
            <p style="font-family: wf_segoe-ui_normal, 'Segoe UI', 'Segoe WP', Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif;">&nbsp;</p>
            <p>
            <!--=""--></p>
            <p>
            </p>
            <p><strong style="color: rgb(86, 160, 211); text-decoration: none;"><a href="http://mj.unc.edu/StemblerLecture2015" class="read-more" style="color: rgb(86, 160, 211); text-decoration: none" target="_blank">READ MORE</a></strong></p>
            <p><strong style="color: rgb(86, 160, 211); text-decoration: none;"><a href="#" class="read-more" style="color: rgb(86, 160, 211); text-decoration: none" target="_blank"><br>
            </a></strong></p>
            </td>
            <td style="padding:0px 15px 0 15px;"><a href="#"></a>
            <h3><span style=" font-size:=" "="" 12px;"=""><a href="http://mj.unc.edu/celebration"><img src="/s/1723/images/gid8/editor/shnsseminar_tnail.png" style="border-top: 8px solid #559fd3" width="300" height="200"></a></span></h3>
            <h4>School celebrates name change, launches Start Here / Never Stop campaign with August event &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</h4>
            <p style="font-family: wf_segoe-ui_normal, 'Segoe UI', 'Segoe WP', Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif; font-size:12px;">The UNC School of Media and Journalism celebrated its new name and kicked off its rebranding campaign with events in Carroll Hall on Aug. 28, 2015 involving students, faculty, staff, alumni and the University community. The school&rsquo;s Start Here / Never Stop tagline captures the idea that what students learn and experience here prepares them for successful careers and transitions in a dynamic media environment.&nbsp;</p>
            <p style="font-family: wf_segoe-ui_normal, 'Segoe UI', 'Segoe WP', Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif;">&nbsp;</p>
            <p><strong style="color: rgb(86, 160, 211);"><a href="http://mj.unc.edu/celebration" class="read-more" style="color: rgb(86, 160, 211); text-decoration: none" target="_blank">READ MORE</a></strong></p>
            <p><strong style="color: rgb(86, 160, 211);"><a href="http://mj.unc.edu/celebration" class="read-more" style="color: rgb(86, 160, 211); text-decoration: none" target="_blank">&nbsp;</a></strong></p>
            </td>
            <td style="padding:0px 15px 0 15px;">
            <h3><a href="http://mj.unc.edu/news/innovation-and-sustainability-community-journalism-focus-new-4-million-unc-school-media-and"><img src="/s/1723/images/gid8/editor/knightgrant.png" alt="" style="border-top: 8px solid #559fd3" width="300" height="200"></a><br>
            </h3>
            <h4>Knight Foundation grant creates $4 million investment supporting innovation and sustainability in local media &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</h4>
            <p>
            </p>
            <p style="font-family: wf_segoe-ui_normal, 'Segoe UI', 'Segoe WP', Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif; font-size:12px;">The UNC School of Media and Journalism will open a research center to explore new models for community news and support the testing and development of innovative digital media products for local news sites. The John S. and James L. Knight Foundation is investing $3 million to launch the research center at the school, with a $1 million match from the University Provost's Office. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>
            <p style="font-family: wf_segoe-ui_normal, 'Segoe UI', 'Segoe WP', Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif;">&nbsp;</p>
            <p>
            </p>
            <p><a href="http://mj.unc.edu/news/innovation-and-sustainability-community-journalism-focus-new-4-million-unc-school-media-and" class="read-more" style="color: rgb(86, 160, 211); text-decoration: none" target="_blank"><strong>READ MORE</strong></a></p>
            <p><a href="#" class="read-more" style="color: rgb(86, 160, 211); text-decoration: none" target="_blank"><strong><br>
